==Turkish==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یاپمق|tr=yapmak|t=to do, make, arrange}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*yap-|t=to make, create, arrange}}.<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM|*jAp-|url=http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2fturcet&text_number=+350&root=config}}</ref> Cognate with {{cog|xqa|tr=yapmāq|t=to build}}, {{cog|oui|tr=yap-|t=to make}}.
===Verb===
{{tr-verb|yapar}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[make]]; to [[build]], [[construct]], [[fashion]]; to [[create]]; to [[manufacture]]; to [[produce]]; to [[prepare]]
#: {{uxi|tr|''Sana kek '''yaptım'''.''|'''I made''' you a cake.}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[do]]; to [[busy]] oneself with, [[act]], [[behave]]
#: {{uxi|tr|''Ödevini '''yaptın mı'''?''|'''Did you do''' your homework?}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[repair]], [[fix]]
#: {{uxi|tr|''Babam bozuk lambayı '''yaptı'''.''|My father '''fixed''' the defective lamp.}}
# {{lb|tr|intransitive|with dative case}} to [[defecate]]
